"Her works function as ‘visual riddles’, unfolding gradually — from the "
"viewer’s initial intuitive impression, through the questions ‘why?’ and ‏or "
"what purpose?’, toward interpretative attempts. This journey may lead to "
"insight or leave the viewer suspended in ambiguity — and that, too, is an "
"intentional part of the artist’s design."
